1 (10) The members of the commission shall not serve on any other regulatory bodies
2 during their terms on the commission.
3 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 278 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary:
6 (1) Except as provided in KRS 164.2807 and 367.150, a person shall not be
7 authorized to intervene as a party to a case before the commission unless the
8 person can demonstrate, by clear and convincing evidence, that the person has a
9 special and unique interest in the specific rates or service of the utility that are at
10 issue in the case;
11 (2) A generalized assertion of an interest of specialized knowledge shall not be
12 sufficient to be granted intervention;
13 (3) Any association seeking to intervene as a party to a case before the commission
14 shall also demonstrate that it satisfies the standards for associational standing set
15 forth by the courts of the Commonwealth; and
16 (4) In cases in which the Attorney General intervenes, he or she shall be the sole
17 advocate for residential consumers in cases before the commission.
18 Section 3. KRS 278.020 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) (a) No person, partnership, public or private corporation, or combination thereof
20 shall commence providing utility service to or for the public or begin the
21 construction of any plant, equipment, property, or facility for furnishing to the
22 public any of the services enumerated in KRS 278.010, except:
23 1. Retail electric suppliers for service connections to electric-consuming
24 facilities located within its certified territory;
25 2. Ordinary extensions of existing systems in the usual course of business;
26 or
27 3. A water district created under KRS Chapter 74 or a water association
