1 formed under KRS Chapter 273 that undertakes a waterline extension or
2 improvement project if the water district or water association is a Class
3 A or B utility as defined in the uniform system of accounts established
4 by the commission according to KRS 278.220 and:
5 a. The water line extension or improvement project will not cost
6 more than five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000); or
7 b. The water district or water association will not, as a result of the
8 water line extension or improvement project, incur obligations
9 requiring commission approval as required by KRS 278.300.
10 In either case, the water district or water association shall not, as a result
11 of the water line extension or improvement project, increase rates to its
12 customers;
13 until that person has obtained from the Public Service Commission a
14 certificate that public convenience and necessity require the service or
15 construction.
16 (b) Upon the filing of an application for a certificate, and after any public hearing
17 which the commission may in its discretion conduct for all interested parties,
18 the commission may issue or refuse to issue the certificate, or issue it in part
19 and refuse it in part, except that the commission shall not refuse or modify an
20 application submitted under KRS 278.023 without consent by the parties to
21 the agreement.
22 (c) The commission, when considering an application for a certificate to construct
23 a base load electric generating facility, may consider the policy of the General
24 Assembly to foster and encourage use of Kentucky coal by electric utilities
25 serving the Commonwealth.
26 (d) The commission, when considering an application for a certificate to construct
27 an electric transmission line, may consider the interstate benefits expected to
Page 4 of 36
XXXX 3/2/2026 9:25 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1957
1 be achieved by the proposed construction or modification of electric
2 transmission facilities in the Commonwealth.
3 (e) Unless exercised within one (1) year from the grant thereof, exclusive of any
4 delay due to the order of any court or failure to obtain any necessary grant or
5 consent, the authority conferred by the issuance of the certificate of
6 convenience and necessity shall be void, but the beginning of any new
7 construction or facility in good faith within the time prescribed by the
8 commission and the prosecution thereof with reasonable diligence shall
9 constitute an exercise of authority under the certificate.
10 (2) For the purposes of this section, construction of any electric transmission line of
11 two hundred (200)[one hundred thirty-eight (138)] kilovolts or more and of more
12 than twenty (20) miles[five thousand two hundred eighty (5,280) feet] in length
13 shall not be considered an ordinary extension of an existing system in the usual
14 course of business and shall require a certificate of public convenience and
15 necessity. However, ordinary extensions of existing systems in the usual course of
16 business not requiring such a certificate shall include:
17 (a) The replacement or upgrading of any existing electric transmission line; or
18 (b) The relocation of any existing electric transmission line to accommodate
19 construction or expansion of a roadway or other transportation infrastructure;
20 or
21 (c) An electric transmission line that is constructed solely to serve a single
22 customer and that will pass over no property other than that owned by the
23 customer to be served.
24 (3) Prior to granting a certificate of public convenience and necessity to construct
25 facilities to provide the services set forth in KRS 278.010(3)(f), the commission
26 shall require the applicant to provide a surety bond, or a reasonable guaranty that
27 the applicant shall operate the facilities in a reasonable and reliable manner for a
