1 period of at least five (5) years. The surety bond or guaranty shall be in an amount
2 sufficient to ensure the full and faithful performance by the applicant or its
3 successors of the obligations and requirements of this chapter and of all applicable
4 federal and state environmental requirements. However, no surety bond or guaranty
5 shall be required for an applicant that is a water district or water association or for
6 an applicant that the commission finds has sufficient assets to ensure the continuity
7 of sewage service.
8 (4) No utility shall exercise any right or privilege under any franchise or permit, after
9 the exercise of that right or privilege has been voluntarily suspended or
10 discontinued for more than one (1) year, without first obtaining from the
11 commission, in the manner provided in subsection (1) of this section, a certificate of
12 convenience and necessity authorizing the exercise of that right or privilege.
13 (5) No utility shall apply for or obtain any franchise, license, or permit from any city or
14 other governmental agency until it has obtained from the commission, in the
15 manner provided in subsection (1) of this section, a certificate of convenience and
16 necessity showing that there is a demand and need for the service sought to be
17 rendered.
18 (6) No person shall acquire or transfer ownership of, or control, or the right to control,
19 any utility under the jurisdiction of the commission by sale of assets, transfer of
20 stock, or otherwise, or abandon the same, without prior approval by the
21 commission. The commission shall grant its approval if the person acquiring the
22 utility has the financial, technical, and managerial abilities to provide reasonable
23 service.
24 (7) No individual, group, syndicate, general or limited partnership, association,
25 corporation, joint stock company, trust, or other entity (an "acquirer"), whether or
26 not organized under the laws of this state, shall acquire control, either directly or
27 indirectly, of any utility furnishing utility service in this state, without having first
Page 6 of 36
XXXX 3/2/2026 9:25 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1957
1 obtained the approval of the commission. Any acquisition of control without prior
2 authorization shall be void and of no effect. As used in this subsection, the term
3 "control" means the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or
4 cause the direction of the management and policies of a utility, whether through the
5 ownership of voting securities, by effecting a change in the composition of the
6 board of directors, by contract or otherwise. Control shall be presumed to exist if
7 any individual or entity, directly or indirectly, owns ten percent (10%) or more of
8 the voting securities of the utility. This presumption may be rebutted by a showing
9 that ownership does not in fact confer control. Application for any approval or
10 authorization shall be made to the commission in writing, verified by oath or
11 affirmation, and be in a form and contain the information as the commission
12 requires. The commission shall approve any proposed acquisition when it finds that
13 the same is to be made in accordance with law, for a proper purpose and is
14 consistent with the public interest. The commission may make investigation and
15 hold hearings in the matter as it deems necessary, and thereafter may grant any
16 application under this subsection in whole or in part and with modification and
17 upon terms and conditions as it deems necessary or appropriate. The commission
18 shall grant, modify, refuse, or prescribe appropriate terms and conditions with
19 respect to every such application within sixty (60) days after the filing of the
20 application therefor, unless it is necessary, for good cause shown, to continue the
21 application for up to sixty (60) additional days. The order continuing the application
22 shall state fully the facts that make continuance necessary. In the absence of that
23 action within that period of time, any proposed acquisition shall be deemed to be
24 approved.
25 (8) Subsection (7) of this section shall not apply to any acquisition of control of any:
26 (a) Utility which derives a greater percentage of its gross revenue from business
27 in another jurisdiction than from business in this state if the commission
Page 7 of 36
XXXX 3/2/2026 9:25 AM Jacketed

