1 determines that the other jurisdiction has statutes or rules which are applicable
2 and are being applied and which afford protection to ratepayers in this state
3 substantially equal to that afforded such ratepayers by subsection (7) of this
4 section;
5 (b) Utility by an acquirer who directly, or indirectly through one (1) or more
6 intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with,
7 the utility, including any entity created at the direction of such utility for
8 purposes of corporate reorganization; or
9 (c) Utility pursuant to the terms of any indebtedness of the utility, provided the
10 issuance of indebtedness was approved by the commission.
11 (9) In a proceeding on an application filed pursuant to this section, any interested
12 person, including a person over whose property the proposed transmission line will
13 cross, may request intervention, and the commission shall, if requested, conduct a
14 public hearing in the county in which the transmission line is proposed to be
15 constructed, or, if the transmission line is proposed to be constructed in more than
16 one county, in one of those counties. The commission shall issue its decision no
17 later than ninety (90) days after the application is filed, unless the commission
18 extends this period, for good cause, to one hundred twenty (120) days. The
19 commission may utilize the provisions of KRS 278.255(3) if, in the exercise of its
20 discretion, it deems it necessary to hire a competent, qualified and independent firm
21 to assist it in reaching its decision. The issuance by the commission of a certificate
22 that public convenience and necessity require the construction of an electric
23 transmission line shall be deemed to be a determination by the commission that, as
24 of the date of issuance, the construction of the line is a prudent investment.
25 (10) The commission shall not approve any application under subsection (6) or (7) of
26 this section for the transfer of control of a utility described in KRS 278.010(3)(f)
27 unless the commission finds, in addition to findings required by those subsections,
