14 Section 5. KRS 278.060 is amended to read as follows:
15 (1) Each commissioner shall be a resident and qualified voter of this state, not less than
16 twenty-five (25) years of age at the time of his or her appointment and
17 qualification, and shall have resided in this state for at least three (3) years prior to
18 his or her appointment and qualification. Each commissioner shall take and
19 subscribe to the constitutional oath of office, which shall be recorded in the office
20 of the Secretary of State.
21 (2) No person shall be appointed to or hold the office of commissioner who holds, or
22 whose immediate family member holds, any official relationship to any utility, or
23 who owns any stocks or bonds thereof, or who has any pecuniary interest therein,
24 except for a pension or retirement savings account if no contributions have been
25 made to it for at least one (1) year prior to the appointment.
26 (3) No commissioner shall receive any rebate, pass, percentage of contract or other
27 thing of value from any utility.
