1 Chairman -- Vacancies.
2 Section 16. (1) On or before July 1, 2026, the Auditor of Public Accounts
3 shall appoint one member of the Public Service Commission for a term expiring July 1,
4 2027, and one member of the Public Service Commission for a term expiring July 1,
5 2028.
6 (2) All current members of the Public Service Commission on the effective date
7 of this Act may serve out the remainder of their terms, provided that they meet the
8 qualification requirements in Sections 1 and 5 of this Act. The term of any current
9 member of the Public Service Commission who does not meet the qualification
10 requirements in Sections 1 and 5 of this Act shall be terminated, and the Governor shall
11 appoint a replacement for the remainder of the term subject to confirmation by the Senate
12 pursuant to Section 1 of this Act.
13 (3) On the effective date of this Act, copies of any records, files, or documents,
14 including legal documents or memoranda, associated with functions of the Public Service
15 Commission that were previously performed by the Energy and Environment Cabinet but
16 for which it is no longer deemed responsible, shall be transferred or transmitted to the
17 Auditor of Public Accounts.
18 Section 17. Whereas it is critical that changes to the organization, membership,
19 and authority of the Public Service Commission be enacted as soon as possible to apply
20 to any membership vacancies or matters before the commission to which the changes
21 may apply, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage
22 and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
